  "response": "Switches, which are commonly used in electrical and electronic circuits, are not typically considered disposable items. They are usually designed to be durable and long-lasting, though they can wear out or break over time and may need to be replaced. When disposing of a switch, it should be done in accordance with local regulations regarding electronic waste (e-waste) to ensure proper recycling or disposal. However, some very small or low-cost switches in certain applications might be considered more disposable if they are used in disposable or limited-use products.",
